    <div xml:id="PN250">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kuykuraṉ malinta koḻuṅtuvai yaṭici</l>
<l>liravalart taṭutta vāyiṟ puravalar</l>
<l>kaṇṇīr taṭutta taṇṇaṟum pantar</l>
<l>kūntal koytu kuṟuntoṭi nīkki</l>
<l>yalli yuṇaviṉ maṉaiviyō ṭiṉiyē</l>
<l>pulleṉ ṟaṉaiyāl vaḷaṅkeḻu tirunakar</l>
<l>vāṉcōṟu koṇṭu tīmpāl vēṇṭu</l>
<l>muṉittalaip putalvar tantai</l>
<l>taṉittalaip peruṅkāṭu muṉṉiya piṉṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>  Rice with fat meat full of plucked ears, (1)</l>
<l>protectors at the door who stopped mendicants, (2)</l>
<l>a cool fragrant pantal that stopped tears [from flowing], (3)</l>
<l>– now, along with the housewife whose food is lily seeds, (5)</l>
<l>having trimmed [her] tresses [and] discarded [her] small bracelets, (4)</l>
<l>you are empty indeed, prosperous brilliant mansion, (6)</l>
<l>after the father of the sons with hateful(?) heads (8)</l>
<l>who need sweet milk with white rice (7)</l>
<l>approached the great wilderness/cremation ground, a lonely area. (9)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
